<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-20-0306 </DOCNO><TEXT>In terms of the Kaluza-Klein theory the authors study some propertiesof the spherically symmetric gravitational field coupled to a masslessscalar field and discuss the final state of the gravitational collapse.The static field with a naked singularity is unstable and generates alarge disturbance of the scalar waves. Even if an event horizon forms,the scalar disturbance continues to develop. This suggests that the extraspace can enlarge with the lapse of time to a visible size near the disturbedblack hole.</TEXT></DOC>